Tailwind Manual

npm init -y
npm install -D tailwindcss
npx tailwindcss init

open tailwind.config.js -> fill content with filename or directory

create src folder -> create input.css file
fill with tailwind directive :
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

npx tailwindcss -i ./src/input.css -o ./dist/output.css --watch

link html with output.css

--- tailwind prettier for consistency ---
npm install -D prettier prettier-plugin-tailwindcss

--- tailwind minify for better size of css file ---
npx tailwindcss -i ./src/input.css -o ./dist/css/final.css --minify
